Emacs has a bug tracker using Debian's bug tracking software.

* http://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/pkgreport.cgi?package=emacs

There is information on reporting and querying bugs from the main page.

* http://debbugs.gnu.org/

Here are some useful preset queries of the bug database.

* [http://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/pkgreport.cgi?package=emacs;include=severity:critical;include=severity:grave;include=severity:serious;include=severity:important Bugs that are marked critical, grave, serious or important.]

* [http://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/pkgreport.cgi?package=emacs;exclude=severity:wishlist;exclude=pending:done;exclude=tags:wontfix Non-wishlist bugs the developers have confirmed]

* [http://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/pkgreport.cgi?package=emacs;include=severity:wishlist;exclude=pending:done;exclude=tags:wontfix Wishlist items under consideration]

* [http://debbugs.gnu.org/cgi/pkgreport.cgi?package=emacs;include=tags:patch;exclude=tags:wontfix Submitted patches]

Discussions about bug counts on the [[emacs-devel]] mailing list:

* 2010-06-23: [http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2010-06/msg00932.html Bug statistics] by Glenn Morris
** [http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2010-06/msg00942.html continued] [http://lists.gnu.org/archive/html/emacs-devel/2010-06/msg00951.html continued]


